                            <comment id="14219150" author="njiang" created="Thu, 20 Nov 2014 09:05:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied the patch into camel master branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16203480" author="igorko" created="Fri, 13 Oct 2017 12:23:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello. This was fixed in initialize() but still present in persistToStore() function&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        Bson updateObj = Updates.set(config.field, lastVal);&lt;br/&gt;
        dbCol.updateOne(trackingObj, updateObj);&lt;br/&gt;
        trackingObj = dbCol.find().first();&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If more then one tracker is present in one collection, after storing lastVal, each trackingObj will replaced by first one from collection. Should be&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        trackingObj = dbCol.find(filter).first();&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Issue present in version 2.20 in both mongodb and mongodb3 component.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
